).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,463,1064]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
This species is widespread throughout the Indo-West Pacific region (
<bibRefCitation author="Guinot" box="[961,1106,932,956]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" refString="Guinot, D. (1976) Constitution de quelques groupes naturels chez les Crustaces Decapodes Brachyoures. I. La superfamille des Bellioidea et trois sous-familles de Xanthidae (Polydectinae Dana, Trichiinae de Haan, Actaeinae Alcock). Memoires du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle, Ser. A, Zoologie, 97, 1 - 308, pls. 1 - 19." type="journal article" year="1976">
Guinot 
<number box="[1046,1106,932,956]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="1976.0">1976</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), although some records of 
<taxonomicName class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Lybia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tessellata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">L. tessellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, particularly from the Hawaiian Islands, are erroneous and are actually for a closely related species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Takeda &amp; Miyake, 1979" authorityName="Takeda &amp; Miyake" authorityYear="1979" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Lybia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="edmondsoni">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">L. edmondsoni</emphasis>
Takeda &amp; Miyake, 
<number box="[511,567,1004,1028]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="1979.0">1979</number>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Castro" box="[627,768,1004,1028]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" refString="Castro, P. (2011) Catalog of the anomuran and brachyuran crabs (Crustacea: Decapoda: Anomura, Brachyura) of the Hawaiian Islands. Zootaxa, 2947, 1 - 154." type="journal article" year="2011">
Castro 
<number box="[708,768,1004,1028]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" value="2011.0">2011</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Surprisingly, no previous scientific records from the 
<collectingCountry name="Philippines" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Philippines</collectingCountry>
of this easily recognizable species have been found.
</paragraph>
